The following commentaries and editorials are also listed on the
main newsfeature budget that moved Wednesday to the general advisory
category. The editor is Carlos Selva in Los Angeles at (213) 237-7832.

Category codes of stories are in parentheses.

NATIONS-COMMENT -- In hearings last week, John Bolton, President
Bush's nominee to be U.S. ambassador to the United Nations, pledged to
``forge a stronger relationship between the United States and the
United Nations''; this kinder, gentler Bolton is exactly what the
United Nations does not need; it needs the radical skepticism of the
old Bolton. 780 words, by Eric A. Posner and John C. Yoo (Times
special). Upcoming.

FEMINISM-COMMENT -- Andrea Dworkin might be only a footnote in the
history of contemporary feminism, but her place in it is assured. 780
words, by Vivan Gornick (Times special) (k). Upcoming.

PINKERTON -- Censors sneak in on little bureaucrat feet. By James
P. Pinkerton (Newsday) (k). Upcoming.

SCHEER -- GOP gays and the ``Finkelstein Phenomenon.'' By Robert
Scheer (Times special) (k). Upcoming.

